    "note": "Tic disorders encompass Tourette syndrome, chronic motor/vocal tic disorder, and provisional tic disorder. Characterized by sudden, rapid, recurrent, nonrhythmic motor movements or vocalizations. Tourette syndrome requires both multiple motor tics and at least one vocal tic for >1 year with onset before age 18. Yale Global Tic Severity Scale (YGTSS) quantifies severity. Habit reversal therapy is first-line behavioral treatment. Pharmacotherapy includes clonidine, guanfacine, and antipsychotics.",
